{"lemma":"حَفِيظَةٍ","slug":"حَفِيظَةٍ","root":"ح.ف.ظ","root_slug":"ح-ف-ظ","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ف-ظ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8507"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8507","headword_ar":"حَفِيظَةٌ","root":"HfZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defence of those persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things, that are sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inviolable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that one is bound to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour, and to defend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from 3, in the first of the senses mentioned above: (K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafaAy^iZu","text_ar":"حَفَايِظُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHafaAy^iZu tu*ohibu AlA^aHoqaAda","text_ar":"الحَفَايِظُ تُذْهِبُ الاَحْقَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanoquDu AlA^aHoqaAda","text_ar":"تَنْقُضُ الاَحْقَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The acts of defending those whom one is bound to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour, and to defend, put away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"annul, rancorous feelings;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e., when thou seest thy relation, or kinsman, wronged, thou defendest him, though rancour be in thy heart. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HifoZapN","text_ar":"حِفْظَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Indignation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of violence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injury, done to something which one is bound to honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect, and to defend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wrong done to a relation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinsman, in one's neighbourhood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the breach of a covenant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaqodirapu tu*ohibu AlHafiyZapa","text_ar":"المَقْدِرَةُ تُذْهِبُ الحَفِيظَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Power"},{"kind":"text","text":"to revenge"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispels anger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indignation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; meaning that it is incumbent to forgive when one has power [to revenge]. (A, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An amulet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a charm, bearing an inscription, which is hung upon a child, to charm against the evil eye &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}